{title: Bloomin' Fools}
{artist: Wilburn Brothers}
{composer: Written by Jimmie Helms and Grant Townsley}

[C]Bloomin' fools only blossom
With the help of neon sunshine on a [G7]stool
Mighty plan sittin' together they'd bloom in smoky weather
And soon they blossom into bloomin' [C]fools
This world is filled with pretty flowers
That grow bigger with each shower
For the rain and the sunhine makes 'em [G7]grow
There's one of every kind but the ones I have in mind
Only blossom where the lights are [C]low
There's a guy on the stool beside me
He'd swear that he's not like me
Although he's been sittin' here since [G7]noon
He's been here for hours and he may not smell like flowers
But that teardrop means he's about to [C]bloom
repeat #1
I hear some folks do their drinkin'
Drivin' round till they're linkin'
Or in some lonely hotel [G7]room
I'll have to beg their pardon for I've got my own garden
It's the only place that I can [C]bloom
repeat #1
[G7]And soon they blossom into bloomin' [C]fools